HEADWORD: Unmechanize
<hw>Un*mech"an*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>mechanize</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To undo the mechanism of; to unmake; <as>as, to
<ex>unmechanize</ex> a structure</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sterne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unmechanized</ent>⟦br⟧
